               <msContents>
                  <summary>Private letter from Longus to Ioulius about urgent business matters which the writer does not want to be widely known; he alludes to some obscure "thirty items;" it is the first document to evidence a precautionary approach to the "idios logos"</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the back the address is also written along the fibers; almost complete</note>
                     <note type="general">27 lines of writing plus 2 lines on the back; the main hand is clear and slightly bent to the right; a second hand writes the address and a third dockets the letter</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
